But on the other everyone is rushing around trying to swerve through tourists, Santa Con nonsense, and grinches.  We tried to go to see some cute Christmasy stuff yesterday but it was so packed with people, we gave up and went to our favorite katsu place.  So basically I will be hibernating in my cute peppermint bedroom until the new year ♥️🎀 Also I am obsessed with this @fashionbrandcompany dress and will be wearing it all year long.  And of course I had to get #glitterthemaltepoo a matching heart collar, and spoiler alert, he hates it 🤣🤣🤣 Happy peppermint season Y’all!

I may only have one lil snagged tooth left, but it’s my best tooth.  I am the softest pup on the planet, but I love laying on even softer blankets and things.  I hate baths more than anything on the planet.  I get the zoomies often, and even at 15, I am still full of energy.  I’m a lil goofy doof but I am also smart as a whip.  I have an incredible internal clock, I wake up everyday at 6:30 on the dot. I am a terrible model, but super photogenic.  My favorite toy is still my first toy, Mr Rabbit.  Hi I’m Glitter have a great nite! 💗💗💗

♥️🎀🧛🏻‍♀️Here’s a cool thing I bought in Japan!
.
Going to the movies in Japan is often more like an event.  So they will usually sell these movie programs or souvenir pamphlets at the theater.  I saw a lot of these in record shops all over Japan.  I thought they were so cool so I bought this one from Bram Stoker’s Dracula because I’m obsessed with the costume design 🎀🧛🏻‍♀️🎀 How cool is that?! I wish we had them here! 
.
.
.

💗 It is with extreme sadness I am sharing the news that our angel baby boy #glitterthemaltepoo crossed over the rainbow bridge yesterday.  He lived an incredible 16 years and was beloved by everyone single person who ever met him 💗 my longest relationship, and one of the two greatest loves of my life.  I will never forget the day I received an email with his photo saying he was available for adoption.  I had been looking for about a year, but as soon as I saw that face, I knew he was meant to adopt me! He was just 10 weeks old!  I was a single dog mom then, so things were quite difficult and he was a rambunctious lil scamp.  But we found our rhythm and eventually found our other soulmate @dimadrjuchin 💗 from then on we were forever a three piece.  He was with us through everything, at our engagement, was the ring bearer at our wedding, and every other milestone along the way.  I really really loved “old man” Glitter.  As a cranky old man from birth, he really grew into the role in his old age.  He followed us everywhere, had a goofy lil personality, the best comedic timing on the planet, and loved crunching leaves on his walks in the park.  He was the softest pup I have ever felt, but loved sleeping on even softer things.  He had a black streak in his ear when we first met that had since turned gray.  He only had one lil snaggle tooth left, but it was his best tooth.  Because he only had one tooth, his lil tongue was always hanging out and it was the most perfect shade of pink.  His favorite toy is still his first toy, Mr Rabbit.  He was the only toy he never destroyed.  Mr Rabbit was with him acting at a pillow at the time of his passing, always and forever there for him.  We were extremely fortunate that he was healthy most of his life with just a few rough days at the end.  We were able to say our goodbyes and then he passed in our arms. 💗 We will never forget you Glitter!  We were SO LUCKY to be yours.  We don’t say goodbye, because we know we will see him again someday.  Rest in peace my beautiful little weirdo.  I love you more than life itself. 💗 Ugh this one is gonna hurt for long time. 
😭😭😭💗💗💗

🎀♥️ Better late than never ♥️🎀🤷🏼‍♀️ 
Haven’t really felt Christmasy this year since we are still heavily grieving the loss of our fur baby Glitter, and with everything going on in the world.  But today I did manage to clean up our bedroom and put up a few decorations.  I’m trying my best and that’s all we can do.  Happy Sunday! 🎀♥️🎀
